column5: Hey guys, I am selling my boat and a few people want to run it in the water does anyone know a free or cheap boat launch somewhere between lake simcoe and GTA that is open with water? I was thinking maybe something in one fo the harbours, but not sure if there slips are open or ice free.
Lake O will probably be your only choice.
Jedi  Holland River in Bradford and at the Queensville sideroad is still solid with Ice.
Is that the quickest to thaw in that area?
Atherley narrows is open but no idea about launches - probably need a crane this time of year!  Michael
Maybe around one of the lake O ports?
Just trailer it up North a bit LOL. The Vernen Narrows and Gull Lake Narrows along the 400 N (Hwy. 11N) were wide open las week.
We launched out of Newcastle a couple of weeks ago and its a short run out to the open lake.
Sixteen Mile Creek, the Credit or Etobicoke Creek all have launches free of ice.
bronte, lasalle, bayfront park, grimsby launch, jordan harbour, pt dalhousie, queenston .... ALL open launches.
Are you sure Bayfront Park is open water? Planning to go this Sunday for ice fishing, please reconfirm?  Thanks
Frenchmans bay is open. You can go off of the beach, and its a little less wavy then the open coast.
Humber river launch, Humber bay park west, Marie Curtis park, lakefront promenade, list goes on for GTA local........or slam the bunny ear muffs on and run her in the driveway
